      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUNAR MOON (4) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Maiden winner three back (22.56) at Warrnambool over 390m. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Key player on best and expected to bounce back. PARK KEY PAW (7) settled midfield in the run and boxed on to finish there when 5th (18.04) at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Must be included in calculations. SWOOPING SEASON (2) was a winner two back when racing on speed but drifted back latest and safely held when 8th and beaten 8 lengths at this track (18.02). Unbeaten from this box in three starts. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. WITHOUT ME (6) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can bounce back.",
